<item>
            <title>[HBASE-12061] Ensure LOG.isXXXEnabled() wrapper around LOG.XXX() calls</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12061</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The common anti-pattern in Java is using LOG.xxx() calls w/o wrapping them into LOG.isXXXEnabled(). This results in unnecessary object serializations/ string concatenations/ garbage object production even if XXX log level is disabled.   &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12743415">HBASE-12061</key>
            <summary>Ensure LOG.isXXXEnabled() wrapper around LOG.XXX() calls</summary>
                <type id="7" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/subtask_alternate.png">Sub-task</type>
